{
  "texts": [
    "Using identity-by-state, we determined that 16.6% of the wheat D genome, corresponding to 666.0 Mb and containing 8,779 high-confidence genes (25.6%), can be covered with Ae.",
    "tauschii L3 haplotype blocks across these landraces (Supplementary Table 17).",
    "Although the proportion of Ae.",
    "tauschii L3 introgressions in most modern bread wheat cultivars is marginal (approximately 1% relative to the entire D genome), the cumulative size of L3 introgressions across multiple bread wheat landraces is considerable.",
    "We determined the complexity and origin of the D genome across 17 hexaploid wheat lines, for which chromosome-scale assemblies are available 11, 34, 40, 41, 20, 42, 43."
  ]
}